Genetic Algorithm IAST
======================
This is the IAST code.
Updated: Tue 29 Sep, 2015, 14:48:35
First version:   Rafael Aguilar, Rocio Bueno
Updated version: Salvador Rodríguez Gómez

Input files:
============
"input", "isoterma1.dat" and "isoterma2.dat"

Fitting:
========
 Genetic Algorithm by the easy way. The hard way is work in progress (branch "genetic")
 Improvement: you can increase the velocity of the fit by decreasing the "GA_POPSIZE" value. It's a BIG number

$ grep -A20 'GA_POPSIZE ini' *.f90
 select case (ajuste)
  case("freundlich")
   npar= 2
   GA_POPSIZE  = 2**14 
  case ("langmuir")
   npar=2
   GA_POPSIZE = 2**14
  case ("toth")
   npar=3
   GA_POPSIZE = 2**18
....
 
 Models:
 -------
$ grep '#model' *.f90
 case("freundlich") !n = a*x**b                                    #model
 case("langmuir")   !n = nmax*alfa*P/(1+alfa*P)                    #model
 case("toth")       !n=f(x)=Nmax*alfa*x/(1+(alfa*x)**c)**(1/c)     #model
 case("jensen")     !n = k1*x/(1+(k1*x/(alfa*(1+k2*x))**c))**(1/c) #model
 case("dubinin_raduschkevich")! N=Nm*exp(-(RT/Eo ln(Po/P))^2)      #model
 case("langmuir_dualsite")    ! N=Nm*b*P/(1+b*P) + Nn*c*P/(1+c*P)  #model
 case("dubinin_astakhov")     ! N=Nm*exp(-(RT/Eo ln(Po/P))^d)      #model

The "dubinin_raduschkevich" and "dubinin_astakhov" models use a thermal parameter.
The default value of the temperature is 298.0 K. You can change this value in the follow line: 
$ grep 'temperature' *.f90
 real,parameter   :: temperature = 298.0

Multicomponent (>2):
====================
 Work in progres (branch "multicomponent").

Installation, Configuration, Usage:
===================================

$ make install
$ make execute
$ make clean

Or just:

$ make all

Example 1:
$ cat input
jensen .true. #<- Isotherm model: langmuir, toth, freundlich, jensen, dubinin_raduschkevich, langmuir_dualsite, dubinin_astakhov.
              # El segundo es un valor logico. Si es .true. el programa realiza el ajuste.
              # En caso contrario no realizará el ajuste y pedirá los parametros en las ultimas lineas en el mismo orden que la fración molar (ejemplo de abajo)
1000          #<- Number of output pressures
0.5           #<- Molar fraction of compound 1 in reservoir
0.5           #<- Molar fraction of compound 2 in reservoir

# The total molar fraction in the mixture has to be equal to 1

$ cat isoterma1.dat
0.01    0.0049446691   <- Pressure and  Loading (arbitrary units)
0.03    0.0166564028
0.06    0.0294963598
0.1     0.0520963225
0.3     0.2009579106
0.6     0.4827990407
1       2.1155133252
3       3.4799668446
6       3.8092907411
10      3.9385998255
....

Example 2: En este ejemplo generamos la curva de la mezcla para un mismo set de parametros calculado anteriormente. Esto es conveniente cuando el modelo es complejo.
$ cat input
langmuir_dualsite .false.
5000
0.10
0.90
4.35646772      0.673587024       6.97058439E-03  0.323694944
0.793254375     3.05414200E-04    0.103873610     3.46274376

